HEADWORD: Phallales
<hw>Phallales</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>An order of fungi comprising
the stinkhorns and related forms whose mature hymenium is slimy and
fetid; sometimes placed in the subclass
<subclass>Homobasidiomycetes</subclass>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> order <ord>Phallales</ord>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phallic</ent>⟦br⟧
